Business Brief -- California Microwave Inc.:
   Profit of Quarter Expected
   To Trail Year-Earlier Level
The estimates were below those of analysts, who had been
looking for third-quarter net of around 29 cents a share,
according to a Zacks Investment survey. In national
over-the-counter trading, stock of the supplier of satellite
earth stations and other communications systems plunged
$3.125 yesterday to close at $12.50 a share.
   The company said earnings for the fiscal year ending June
30 would be close to the $8 million, or 93 cents a share,
earned a year earlier, when sales were $177.4 million.